<title>NETHERLANDS: VOLKER, NBM FINALISE RAIL DEAL.</title>
<headline>VOLKER, NBM FINALISE RAIL DEAL.</headline>
<dateline>ROTTERDAM 1997-08-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dutch builders Volker Wessels Stevin and NBM Amstelland will take over part of the rail construction activities of state-owned Dutch Railways (NS), the NS said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>The company said in February it was in talks with the construction firms and it expected to reach an agreement.</p>
<p>The NS said about 30 percent of its maintenance, breakdown and rail-infrastructure business would go to Volker and about 20 percent to NBM.</p>
<p>The other half would be transferred to the Strukton Group, a fully-owned construction subsidiary of the NS.</p>
